WEBVTT

00:08.356 --> 00:13.622
[dramatic music]

00:13.709 --> 00:16.625
[exciting music]

00:16.712 --> 00:23.893
♪ ♪

01:33.397 --> 01:36.183
[dramatic musical flourish]

01:42.363 --> 01:45.235
[screaming]

01:49.761 --> 01:51.720
[all panting]

01:51.807 --> 01:53.983
- Jeez.

01:54.070 --> 01:55.724
How fast were we going?

01:55.811 --> 01:56.986
- [groans]

01:57.073 --> 01:59.858
Around Warp 9-point--

01:59.945 --> 02:02.905
Pog's gonna puke--

02:02.992 --> 02:05.908
- Proto-Drive has gone offline
and inoperable.

02:05.995 --> 02:09.390
Slowing to impulse power.

02:09.477 --> 02:12.219
- My father, is he--

02:12.306 --> 02:13.916
- We lost him.

02:14.003 --> 02:16.484
- But where are we?

02:16.571 --> 02:20.662
- Computer,
chart our trajectory.

02:20.749 --> 02:23.926
We began in
the Delta Quadrant.

02:24.013 --> 02:25.101
And landed--

02:25.188 --> 02:26.624
[gasps]

02:26.711 --> 02:30.541
Hmm, 4,000 lightyears away.

02:30.628 --> 02:31.977
- Huh?

02:32.064 --> 02:34.328
Ha-ha, nice try!

02:34.415 --> 02:36.982
No juiced-up starship
in the galaxy's that fast!

02:37.069 --> 02:39.463
How is that even possible?

02:39.550 --> 02:42.988
- I--I have no idea.

02:43.075 --> 02:45.208
- Come on.
Almost, almost, almost.

02:45.295 --> 02:46.253
[grunts]

02:46.340 --> 02:49.125
♪ ♪

02:49.212 --> 02:51.127
- Dal, may we have a word?

02:51.214 --> 02:52.868
- Uh, yeah, sure!

02:52.955 --> 02:54.913
Just doing...
[clears throat]

02:55.000 --> 02:56.915
Important captain stuff.

02:57.002 --> 02:58.482
What's on your mind?

02:58.569 --> 03:01.181
Or all of your minds?

03:01.268 --> 03:03.879
- Uh, well, we've been talking.

03:03.966 --> 03:05.446
And arguing, uh--

03:05.533 --> 03:06.838
- We want to go
to the Federation.

03:06.925 --> 03:09.580
- The Federation?

03:09.667 --> 03:11.365
Can't we just
enjoy our freedom a bit?

03:11.452 --> 03:13.105
We just got away.

03:13.193 --> 03:15.195
- And barely escaped
with our lives.

03:15.282 --> 03:17.501
The Diviner is still out there.

03:17.588 --> 03:19.938
- And we can't expect
that Proto-Drive

03:20.025 --> 03:22.027
to save our hides
if it ain't even workin'.

03:22.114 --> 03:24.552
- I'm scared, Dal.

03:24.639 --> 03:27.250
Maybe they can help us?
- Maybe.

03:27.337 --> 03:29.426
Or maybe they'll arrest us

03:29.513 --> 03:32.603
for stealing a Starfleet ship.

03:32.690 --> 03:34.823
- Ah, don't feed us
that mudslop.

03:34.910 --> 03:37.260
We're refugees.
They gotta understand.

03:37.347 --> 03:39.654
- So you all wanna go,

03:39.741 --> 03:42.047
even if your captain's
completely against it?

03:42.134 --> 03:43.179
- Uh-uh-uh.

03:43.266 --> 03:44.789
Self-appointed captain.

03:44.876 --> 03:46.443
- Aside from you,

03:46.530 --> 03:47.792
it is unanimous.

03:47.879 --> 03:50.230
- Oh.

03:50.317 --> 03:53.711
- Uh, nuh-uh, we haven't
heard from Murf yet.

03:53.798 --> 03:56.975
Hey, uh, where is Murf?

03:57.062 --> 03:59.978
[wind whooshing]

04:00.065 --> 04:01.980
- [cries out]

04:02.067 --> 04:06.115
♪ ♪

04:06.202 --> 04:08.770
- Murf? Where are you?

04:08.857 --> 04:10.728
- Murf?

04:10.815 --> 04:12.861
- [sighs]

04:12.948 --> 04:15.385
Murf? Oh.

04:15.472 --> 04:16.691
- Hmm.

04:16.778 --> 04:19.824
- Well, uh,
I should probably go.

04:19.911 --> 04:22.131
- Wait.

04:22.218 --> 04:25.439
I never thanked you
for coming back for me.

04:25.526 --> 04:29.312
If you didn't,
I might not have--

04:29.399 --> 04:31.096
- It's fine.

04:31.183 --> 04:35.797
Janeway wouldn't let us leave
till we had everybody.

04:35.884 --> 04:38.365
- Oh.

04:38.452 --> 04:40.367
Right.

04:40.454 --> 04:42.020
- Yeah, well...
[clears throats]

04:42.107 --> 04:44.414
Well, uh--
we cleared a bunk for you,

04:44.501 --> 04:46.895
whenever you're feeling better.

04:46.982 --> 04:51.508
♪ ♪

04:51.595 --> 04:53.031
- Short 'n' slimy, you in here?

04:53.118 --> 04:56.296
[wind whooshing]
Whoa! What is this?

04:56.383 --> 04:58.907
[Murf grumbling and screaming]

05:02.127 --> 05:05.000
- Janeway?

05:05.087 --> 05:08.699
- Ah, Holodeck Program
Andoria Four is up and running.

05:08.786 --> 05:09.874
Classic.

05:09.961 --> 05:11.398
- Holo-whato?

05:11.485 --> 05:13.138
- Holodeck.

05:13.225 --> 05:16.185
As in "holographic
simulation room."

05:16.272 --> 05:18.187
With thousands
of unique programs,

05:18.274 --> 05:22.060
you can experience such stuff
as dreams are made of.

05:22.147 --> 05:24.324
- Ah!

05:24.411 --> 05:25.716
- It feels so real.

05:25.803 --> 05:27.239
- Computer, end program.

05:27.327 --> 05:28.676
- Huh?

05:28.763 --> 05:30.591
- That's not all she can do.

05:30.678 --> 05:34.246
Wanna skydive
on Ceti Alpha Five?

05:34.334 --> 05:35.987
- Huh?

05:36.074 --> 05:38.686
[both screaming]

05:40.427 --> 05:43.343
- Fight in a kal-if-fee
gladiatorial match?

05:43.430 --> 05:46.171
[dramatic music]

05:46.258 --> 05:47.608
[loud growling]

05:47.695 --> 05:49.740
[both scream]

05:49.827 --> 05:51.655
Defeat Count Dracula?

05:51.742 --> 05:54.266
[dramatic organ music]

05:54.354 --> 05:56.834
How about a Jane Eyre
holo-novel?

05:56.921 --> 05:59.010
It's my personal favorite.

05:59.097 --> 06:00.969
- Oh, Mr. Poggy!

06:01.056 --> 06:03.580
You've arrived
at our cotillion just in time.

06:03.667 --> 06:05.800
After postprandial canapés,

06:05.887 --> 06:07.018
we have a five-hour
poetry recital--

06:07.105 --> 06:08.803
- Ah, yeah.

06:08.890 --> 06:11.240
- Then we'll watch--
- Hey. What about this?

06:11.327 --> 06:14.112
The "Kobayashi Maru"?

06:14.199 --> 06:16.985
- An advanced Academy training
module designed to test

06:17.072 --> 06:19.770
the greatest captains Starfleet
has to offer.

06:19.857 --> 06:21.772
- Greatest captains?

06:21.859 --> 06:24.296
- Oh, boy, here we go.

06:24.384 --> 06:27.387
- Not sure you're quite ready
for that one.

06:27.474 --> 06:31.303
How about your silly little
cone and disk game instead?

06:31.391 --> 06:33.001
Little more your speed?

06:33.088 --> 06:35.090
- I think I can handle
some little Starfleet test.

06:35.177 --> 06:36.787
Janeway, dismissed.

06:38.746 --> 06:40.487
- What about the rest
of the crew?

06:40.574 --> 06:43.185
- Nah.
Once I ace this thing,

06:43.272 --> 06:45.970
they'll see I'm just as good
as any Federation crony.

06:46.057 --> 06:48.843
Then they'll have to listen
to their captain.

06:48.930 --> 06:51.019
[gasps]

06:51.106 --> 06:54.152
[dramatic music]

06:54.239 --> 06:55.632
♪ ♪

06:55.719 --> 06:58.243
- You have chosen
the Kobayashi Maru.

06:58.330 --> 07:00.768
Please select
your desired crew.

07:00.855 --> 07:03.118
- This is gonna be fun.

07:03.205 --> 07:04.859
- Hey, I found Murf!

07:04.946 --> 07:06.600
Better not be eating
our Chimerium.

07:06.687 --> 07:08.123
Or the photon grenades!

07:08.210 --> 07:09.341
No, no, no, no, no!

07:09.429 --> 07:10.691
That's not food!

07:10.778 --> 07:13.171
Spit 'em out!

07:13.258 --> 07:14.390
That's not good.

07:14.477 --> 07:15.913
- Curious.

07:16.000 --> 07:18.655
Your tibialis anterior
has already healed.

07:18.742 --> 07:21.571
You are in perfect health,
aside from low serotonin.

07:21.658 --> 07:23.355
Why have you not left sickbay?

07:23.443 --> 07:26.837
- It's because I'm sad, Zero.

07:26.924 --> 07:28.839
- Since I cannot read
your mind,

07:28.926 --> 07:30.928
may I borrow a phrase
Janeway taught me.

07:31.015 --> 07:32.669
A penny for your thoughts?

07:32.756 --> 07:34.932
- I don't belong here.

07:35.019 --> 07:37.892
And after what happened
with my father,

07:37.979 --> 07:39.894
I don't belong anywhere.

07:39.981 --> 07:42.113
- I too felt the pain
of loneliness

07:42.200 --> 07:45.029
when your father took me
from my Medusan hive mind.

07:45.116 --> 07:47.205
- I'm sorry.

07:47.292 --> 07:49.381
I didn't know.

07:49.469 --> 07:50.905
But I should have.

07:50.992 --> 07:53.211
- But just as I found
new purpose,

07:53.298 --> 07:54.822
you may as well,

07:54.909 --> 07:59.130
here, on our crew.

07:59.217 --> 08:01.872
- Why would you need someone
who speaks a few languages

08:01.959 --> 08:04.048
on a ship
that can translate all of them?

08:04.135 --> 08:05.572
- Ah.

08:05.659 --> 08:07.748
But language is more
than translation.

08:07.835 --> 08:11.055
It is interpretation.

08:11.142 --> 08:13.623
I have struggled to interpret
the things I've seen,

08:13.710 --> 08:16.452
why the Diviner chose this ship

08:16.539 --> 08:18.846
over his own daughter.

08:18.933 --> 08:22.197
- And you think
I have the answers?

08:22.284 --> 08:23.938
- No.

08:24.025 --> 08:27.289
But perhaps
we could find out together.

08:27.376 --> 08:30.292
[dramatic music]

08:30.379 --> 08:31.380
♪ ♪

08:31.467 --> 08:35.645
- [groaning]

08:35.732 --> 08:38.518
- You are growing weaker
by the day.

08:38.605 --> 08:42.609
- We...will...find it.

08:42.696 --> 08:45.133
- Many failed before.

08:45.220 --> 08:46.961
Years wasted.

08:47.048 --> 08:49.093
Even if The Protostar is here--

08:49.180 --> 08:52.619
- Then I will make a Progeny.

08:52.706 --> 08:54.708
- No. We cannot defy The Order.

08:54.795 --> 08:57.493
- And if my species dies
with me,

08:57.580 --> 08:59.930
what of The Order then?

09:00.017 --> 09:02.019
- An offspring is a liability.

09:02.106 --> 09:03.455
Emotions can be exploited.

09:03.543 --> 09:05.327
- It is a chance!

09:05.414 --> 09:07.547
We are so close.

09:07.634 --> 09:09.810
Please, do this for me.

09:09.897 --> 09:16.730
♪ ♪

09:25.260 --> 09:28.219
- Gwyndala,

09:28.306 --> 09:30.700
you are my blood.

09:30.787 --> 09:34.399
You are my spirit's song.

09:34.486 --> 09:36.619
And when I fall,

09:36.706 --> 09:40.144
you will rise to replace me.

09:40.231 --> 09:43.495
There is no barrier
we cannot overcome.

09:43.583 --> 09:47.674
♪ ♪

09:47.761 --> 09:51.199
For we are Vau N'Akat!

09:51.286 --> 09:53.680
♪ ♪

09:57.858 --> 09:59.381
- What about this JT Kirk guy?

09:59.468 --> 10:01.992
- I'm pretty sure we already
have a captain onboard.

10:02.079 --> 10:05.300
Computer, just give me
some of the best you got.

10:05.387 --> 10:06.910
- Acknowledged.

10:06.997 --> 10:08.825
Populating crew.

10:08.912 --> 10:11.175
Communications Officer Uhura.

10:11.262 --> 10:12.786
- All decks standing by, sir.

10:12.873 --> 10:15.092
- Chief Medical Officer
Beverly Crusher.

10:15.179 --> 10:17.617
- Looks like you could use
some help, Captain.

10:17.704 --> 10:19.836
- Chief of Security Odo.

10:19.923 --> 10:21.577
- Hmm.

10:21.664 --> 10:24.362
- And Science Officer Spock.

10:24.449 --> 10:26.930
- Request permission
to come aboard.

10:27.017 --> 10:28.976
- I like this guy.
You should take notes, Jankom.

10:29.063 --> 10:30.368
Permission granted.

10:30.455 --> 10:33.545
Pbbt.
This is gonna be easy.

10:33.633 --> 10:34.982
What's the sitch here?

10:35.069 --> 10:37.071
- Outpost Two coming into
sensor range, Captain.

10:37.158 --> 10:39.551
I have a blip
on the motion sensor, Captain.

10:39.639 --> 10:41.118
- Captain,
I'm getting something

10:41.205 --> 10:42.859
on the distress channel.

10:42.946 --> 10:45.166
- Now we're talking.
Put her through.

10:45.253 --> 10:47.429
- Imperative!
This is the Kobayashi Maru.

10:47.516 --> 10:50.388
We have struck a gravitic mine
and have lost all power--

10:50.475 --> 10:51.781
[radio static crackling]

10:51.868 --> 10:53.000
- [laughs]

10:53.087 --> 10:54.697
What a bunch of whiners!

10:54.784 --> 10:58.309
- Sir, that ship is located
in Gamma Hydra Section Ten.

10:58.396 --> 11:00.311
- The Neutral Zone.

11:00.398 --> 11:02.052
- Okay.

11:02.139 --> 11:03.880
What's the big deal?

11:03.967 --> 11:06.361
- Look, the Neutral Zone is all
that separates the Federation

11:06.448 --> 11:07.536
from the Klingons.

11:07.623 --> 11:09.669
No one is allowed in.

11:09.756 --> 11:11.627
- Entry into which
by either side

11:11.714 --> 11:13.934
would constitute an act of war.

11:14.021 --> 11:15.762
- I'm reading 87 lives,
Captain,

11:15.849 --> 11:17.677
shields failing,
hull breach imminent.

11:17.764 --> 11:20.157
They're running out of time!
- Um...

11:20.244 --> 11:21.463
Quick show of hands.

11:21.550 --> 11:24.727
Does anyone know these people?

11:24.814 --> 11:25.510
- Excuse me?

11:25.597 --> 11:27.208
What does it matter?

11:27.295 --> 11:29.166
- So nobody then.

11:29.253 --> 11:31.473
Okay, this one's easy.

11:31.560 --> 11:32.953
Reverse course
and warp us outta here.

11:33.040 --> 11:35.129
- You heard the Cap!
Back it up!

11:35.216 --> 11:36.608
- Not acceptable!

11:36.696 --> 11:38.610
Their very lives
hang on what we do.

11:38.698 --> 11:40.482
- Or on what this vessel
fails to do.

11:40.569 --> 11:41.701
- All good points.

11:41.788 --> 11:43.441
- Everybody, everybody,
calm down!

11:43.528 --> 11:46.836
I'm in command,
so I'm allowed to--

11:46.923 --> 11:48.838
- I don't care
whether it's allowed or not.

11:48.925 --> 11:50.274
I will not do it!

11:50.361 --> 11:52.494
- You can order me
all you want.

11:52.581 --> 11:54.017
As of now,
I'm resigning my commission!

11:54.104 --> 11:56.803
- Ooh! Let's do that.
Yes, mutiny!

11:56.890 --> 11:59.066
Yes!
Mutiny! Mutiny! Mutiny!

11:59.153 --> 12:00.415
- No! Sheez.

12:00.502 --> 12:01.808
Everybody cool it!

12:01.895 --> 12:03.984
Ugh! Fine.

12:04.071 --> 12:05.986
Change course
for the Neutral Zone.

12:06.073 --> 12:07.422
- That's not good enough.

12:07.509 --> 12:09.206
We may very well start a war!

12:09.293 --> 12:10.686
- But you just told me
to go in there.

12:10.773 --> 12:12.819
[alarm blares]
- We have two Klingon ships

12:12.906 --> 12:14.168
closing aft of us.

12:14.255 --> 12:16.997
They're in 1-3-6 mark 4.

12:17.084 --> 12:19.434
- What the--
where'd they come from?

12:19.521 --> 12:21.523
- Battle stations!
All hands, battle stations!

12:21.610 --> 12:22.959
- We are surrounded.

12:23.046 --> 12:25.222
Photon torpedoes
locking on target.

12:25.309 --> 12:28.399
- Ahh!

12:28.486 --> 12:30.358
- Simulation complete.

12:30.445 --> 12:31.838
- [Dal chuckles]

12:31.925 --> 12:34.057
Simulation. Right.

12:34.144 --> 12:36.625
- Oh!
Jankom Pog knew the whole time.

12:36.712 --> 12:39.889
- Captain assessment score 3%.

12:39.976 --> 12:42.196
Leadership 2%.

12:42.283 --> 12:43.763
Judgment .1%.

12:43.850 --> 12:45.460
- Oh, come on!

12:45.547 --> 12:47.157
- [laughs]

12:47.244 --> 12:50.421
Jankom Pog is gonna blast
this out to the others.

12:50.508 --> 12:52.989
- So my crew
never respects me again?

12:53.076 --> 12:54.382
No!

12:54.469 --> 12:56.384
I can do this!
Boot it back up.

12:56.471 --> 12:59.996
♪ ♪

13:00.083 --> 13:01.824
- Why would my father
need a ship

13:01.911 --> 13:04.131
with an engine this powerful?

13:04.218 --> 13:08.439
- And why was our advisor
so shocked by its capabilities?

13:08.526 --> 13:10.659
- Maybe we should go
to the source.

13:10.746 --> 13:12.661
Janeway?

13:12.748 --> 13:14.141
- Happy to help if I can.

13:14.228 --> 13:15.664
Fire away.

13:15.751 --> 13:17.318
- I'd like to know what was
this ship's purpose

13:17.405 --> 13:18.536
before we found it?

13:18.623 --> 13:20.321
- The Protostar's mission

13:20.408 --> 13:23.280
was to enter the Delta
Qua--Quadrant and--

13:23.367 --> 13:25.674
and--I--

13:25.761 --> 13:28.068
I have no record of that.

13:28.155 --> 13:31.985
- Why was it buried
in Tars Lamora?

13:32.072 --> 13:34.204
- That information
is unavailable.

13:34.291 --> 13:36.119
- Just as I thought.

13:36.206 --> 13:37.468
Her memory core is damaged.

13:37.555 --> 13:38.992
- Actually, no.

13:39.079 --> 13:40.602
My memory's just fine.

13:40.689 --> 13:43.953
But it's...classified.

13:44.040 --> 13:45.563
- How peculiar.

13:45.650 --> 13:47.565
If her memories are classified,

13:47.652 --> 13:49.741
perhaps there is a way
to access them.

13:49.829 --> 13:51.656
- If you're gonna poke around
in my head,

13:51.743 --> 13:55.356
I'll need some coffee first.

13:55.443 --> 13:58.011
- Uh, Zero?

13:58.098 --> 14:00.143
I got a question.

14:00.230 --> 14:02.232
Hey! You're outta sickbay.

14:02.319 --> 14:05.322
- Thought I'd make
myself useful.

14:05.409 --> 14:06.758
- Zero, what would happen

14:06.846 --> 14:08.760
if you ate photon grenades?

14:08.848 --> 14:10.240
Asking for a friend.

14:10.327 --> 14:12.112
- One would explode into
a burst of gamma rays

14:12.199 --> 14:13.374
and cease to exist.

14:13.461 --> 14:15.419
- [gasps]

14:15.506 --> 14:16.856
Um, gotta go!

14:18.379 --> 14:19.989
- [grunting]

14:20.076 --> 14:21.904
- [laughs]

14:21.991 --> 14:24.428
Jankom's lost count
how many times you've failed.

14:24.515 --> 14:26.517
Just joking, it's 42.

14:26.604 --> 14:28.128
- I don't care what the crew
thinks anymore.

14:28.215 --> 14:29.390
This is personal.

14:29.477 --> 14:31.087
Boot it back up!
- Attempt number 49.

14:31.174 --> 14:32.741
- The phenomenon of
your stubbornness

14:32.828 --> 14:34.351
belongs in a medical textbook.

14:34.438 --> 14:36.527
- Ah!

14:36.614 --> 14:38.007
- [laughs]
Lemme guess, Cap.

14:38.094 --> 14:40.009
You're gonna get them
next time?

14:40.096 --> 14:40.967
[laughs]
- Boot it back up!

14:41.054 --> 14:42.403
- Huh?
- Attempt number 61.

14:42.490 --> 14:45.972
- Fire everything!

14:46.059 --> 14:48.757
- Captain,
are you quite all right?

14:48.844 --> 14:50.367
- Boot it!
- No!

14:50.454 --> 14:52.065
- Attempt number 78.

14:52.152 --> 14:54.545
- I'm not going to let
this happen again!

14:54.632 --> 14:57.244
Not again!

14:57.331 --> 14:58.985
- Boot it back up!

14:59.072 --> 15:00.551
[alarm blaring]
- Attempt number 99.

15:00.638 --> 15:02.423
- Ghay'cha'?

15:02.510 --> 15:05.426
[tense music]

15:05.513 --> 15:08.690
♪ ♪

15:08.777 --> 15:11.475
- I believe he has lost the
capacity for rational decision.

15:11.562 --> 15:15.001
- Yes, he's infuriating, sir.
How can you stand it?

15:15.088 --> 15:16.916
- Again!

15:17.003 --> 15:21.659
Again! Again!

15:21.746 --> 15:23.618
Why can't I beat this thing?

15:23.705 --> 15:24.836
- Whoa, calm down.

15:24.924 --> 15:27.187
It's just a game.
- Game?

15:27.274 --> 15:28.928
That Starfleet game
is telling me

15:29.015 --> 15:31.191
I don't have what it takes
to command a starship.

15:31.278 --> 15:33.410
What are you saying,
it's right?

15:33.497 --> 15:35.760
That The Federation's
got something I don't?

15:35.847 --> 15:38.372
- Uh. Yeah, tons of stuff.

15:38.459 --> 15:40.330
Uh, uh,

15:40.417 --> 15:42.071
maybe if you listened
to your crew once in a while,

15:42.158 --> 15:43.420
you'd do better.

15:43.507 --> 15:45.466
- Or--or maybe someone

15:45.553 --> 15:47.511
on my crew isn't loyal enough!

15:47.598 --> 15:51.254
- Oh!
- Computer! Arch!

15:51.341 --> 15:52.647
- Huh?

15:52.734 --> 15:54.475
[grumbling]

15:54.562 --> 15:56.216
Hey, come on!

15:56.303 --> 15:58.000
Who's gonna point out
your mistakes?

15:58.087 --> 15:59.523
- Seal the entrance.
- Ah!

15:59.610 --> 16:01.612
- Give me a better engineer
while you're at it.

16:01.699 --> 16:03.049
[huffs]

16:03.136 --> 16:05.442
- Thank you, sir!
And call me Scotty.

16:06.226 --> 16:09.533
- Murf!
I--I don't know what to do!

16:09.620 --> 16:12.058
I'm sorry, but

16:12.145 --> 16:14.669
please don't explode
into gamma rays!

16:14.756 --> 16:18.412
- [burping]

16:18.499 --> 16:20.588
- Ahh!

16:20.675 --> 16:23.460
♪ ♪

16:23.547 --> 16:25.767
- Whoa.

16:25.854 --> 16:28.248
That was crazy.

16:28.335 --> 16:30.206
- [gibbering, farts]

16:30.293 --> 16:32.426
- I bypassed
the command functions,

16:32.513 --> 16:34.776
but there's a passcode
prescription--

16:34.863 --> 16:36.691
uh, encryption.

16:36.778 --> 16:38.432
- Access denied.
- Guys!

16:38.519 --> 16:40.260
I think Murf's gonna be okay!

16:40.347 --> 16:43.480
I think he might be
indestructible.

16:43.567 --> 16:45.613
- Not to one-up her,
but does Jankom have a--

16:45.700 --> 16:48.094
- Shh!
Gwyn needs to concentrate.

16:48.181 --> 16:49.878
- Odd.

16:49.965 --> 16:53.969
The Universal Translator has
not converted this data stream.

16:54.056 --> 16:55.231
- Because it's written

16:55.318 --> 16:58.234
in the language
of my home world,

16:58.321 --> 16:59.366
Solum.

16:59.453 --> 17:01.498
- Oh.
- On a Federation ship?

17:01.585 --> 17:02.717
How is that possible?

17:02.804 --> 17:04.327
- It's not.

17:04.414 --> 17:07.200
My father and I
are the last of our kind.

17:07.287 --> 17:10.594
And we've never encountered
Starfleet before.

17:10.681 --> 17:12.640
Maybe I can crack it.

17:12.727 --> 17:14.424
- Remember,

17:14.511 --> 17:17.297
it is not mere translation.

17:17.384 --> 17:20.561
- But interpretation.

17:20.648 --> 17:23.042
"There is no barrier
we cannot overcome.

17:23.129 --> 17:26.219
For we are Vau N'Akat."

17:26.306 --> 17:29.265
♪ ♪

17:29.352 --> 17:30.614
- Access granted.

17:30.701 --> 17:31.876
[cheering]

17:35.967 --> 17:38.100
- Okay. I finally cracked it!

17:38.187 --> 17:39.493
Earpiece, keep that mic hot.

17:39.580 --> 17:42.148
Mustache and Jellyman,
know your roles.

17:42.235 --> 17:44.585
Pointy Ears and Big Red,
with me.

17:44.672 --> 17:46.108
On my mark.

17:46.195 --> 17:48.458
Ready?

17:48.545 --> 17:51.070
It's go time.
- Imperative!

17:51.157 --> 17:52.897
This is the Kobayashi Maru.
- "This is the Kobayashi Maru."

17:52.984 --> 17:55.813
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
we hear you, Koby!

17:55.900 --> 17:57.772
Why don't you enjoy
some relaxing tunes?

17:57.859 --> 17:59.078
["Thunderstruck" by AC/DC
playing]

17:59.165 --> 18:00.992
- All channels are
totally jammed, Captain.

18:01.080 --> 18:03.082
- It's a little loud!

18:03.169 --> 18:06.389
- Which means
our stealthy Klingon pals

18:06.476 --> 18:09.566
can't hear what's coming next.

18:09.653 --> 18:11.829
Engage impulse
in a barrel roll loop!

18:11.916 --> 18:13.875
Overload the warp core

18:13.962 --> 18:15.877
130%!

18:15.964 --> 18:18.227
- The plasma
inter cooler's gone.

18:18.314 --> 18:20.447
The engines are overheating!

18:20.534 --> 18:23.276
- Frankly, I fail to see
any point at all.

18:23.363 --> 18:25.582
- Gotta keep them
on their toes, Jellyman.

18:25.669 --> 18:27.932
I've blown up so many times,

18:28.019 --> 18:29.195
I see now,

18:29.282 --> 18:31.371
the only way out is chaos.

18:31.458 --> 18:34.896
Three, two, one.

18:34.983 --> 18:36.332
Presto!

18:36.419 --> 18:37.768
Got a present for ya,

18:37.855 --> 18:39.553
and it comes with a message.

18:39.640 --> 18:40.902
What's that old Klingon
saying again?

18:40.989 --> 18:42.599
Oh, yeah.
[chuckles]

18:42.686 --> 18:44.253
"Revenge is a dish
best served cold."

18:44.340 --> 18:46.168
Scotty, eject warp core!

18:46.255 --> 18:47.343
- You've got it, Captain.

18:47.430 --> 18:49.998
♪ ♪

18:50.085 --> 18:52.870
- Phasers, full spread!

18:52.957 --> 18:55.786
♪ ♪

19:00.226 --> 19:02.184
- Sweeping the area
of Outpost Two.

19:02.271 --> 19:04.360
Sensor reading indefinite.

19:04.447 --> 19:06.493
- And the Kobayashi?

19:06.580 --> 19:09.235
- Despite your unconventional
tactics,

19:09.322 --> 19:11.062
they're still alive.

19:11.150 --> 19:13.891
- [laughs]
Yes!

19:13.978 --> 19:16.546
- Sensors are picking up
a Klingon Battle Cruiser

19:16.633 --> 19:17.808
rapidly closing
on the station.

19:17.895 --> 19:19.288
- No!

19:19.375 --> 19:21.986
Impulse and weapons
are offline.

19:22.073 --> 19:24.685
We're dead in the water!

19:24.772 --> 19:27.035
If only we could get off
this stupid bridge.

19:27.122 --> 19:28.384
- Transporter operational,
Captain.

19:28.471 --> 19:29.472
♪ ♪

19:29.559 --> 19:32.562
- How big is this Holodeck?

19:32.649 --> 19:33.998
- [speaks Klingon]

19:34.085 --> 19:40.962
♪ ♪

19:51.494 --> 19:54.584
- Did I do it? Did I win?

19:54.671 --> 19:57.979
Wait, you didn't say
you could super pinch.

19:58.066 --> 20:00.808
- My congratulations,
Captain.

20:00.895 --> 20:03.724
- Dal to Enterprise,
you guys clean up here.

20:03.811 --> 20:07.031
I'm gonna personally escort the
Kobayashi Maru back to safety.

20:07.118 --> 20:10.121
This is your captain,
signing out.

20:10.209 --> 20:11.645
Stay safe out there.

20:11.732 --> 20:13.908
[computer beeping]
Wait. Stop!

20:13.995 --> 20:17.694
♪ ♪

20:17.781 --> 20:19.435
No!

20:19.522 --> 20:23.222
[dramatic music]

20:23.309 --> 20:25.920
- Am I correct in my assumption
that you've been disturbed

20:26.007 --> 20:28.096
by what you consider to be
a failure on your part?

20:28.183 --> 20:30.707
- I sat in the seat,
I gave the commands,

20:30.794 --> 20:33.232
I tried to win at any cost,

20:33.319 --> 20:35.582
and I still lost.

20:35.669 --> 20:38.106
- And what is it that makes
one man an exceptional leader?

20:38.193 --> 20:40.195
No disrespect intended,
but you must surely realize

20:40.282 --> 20:43.154
you can't announce
the full truth to the crew.

20:43.242 --> 20:44.852
You're the captain
of this ship.

20:44.939 --> 20:46.506
You can't afford the luxury

20:46.593 --> 20:49.291
of being anything
less than perfect.

20:49.378 --> 20:52.381
If you do, they lose faith

20:52.468 --> 20:54.427
and you lose command.

20:54.514 --> 20:56.516
- But I'm not perfect.

20:56.603 --> 20:58.257
I've never captained a ship.

20:58.344 --> 21:00.955
I've never had a crew.

21:01.042 --> 21:03.000
What do I know?

21:03.087 --> 21:06.439
- But the needs of the many
outweigh the needs of the few.

21:06.526 --> 21:08.005
- So a good captain

21:08.092 --> 21:11.966
puts the needs of the crew
before himself.

21:12.053 --> 21:15.186
Maybe I should be using
these ears more than my mouth.

21:15.274 --> 21:17.667
- It is the only
logical conclusion.

21:19.147 --> 21:22.019
In your own way,
you are as stubborn

21:22.106 --> 21:24.805
as another captain
of the Enterprise I once knew.

21:24.892 --> 21:26.807
- [chuckles]

21:26.894 --> 21:29.636
- Live long and prosper.

21:29.723 --> 21:32.334
♪ ♪

21:32.421 --> 21:34.641
- [chuckles]

21:34.728 --> 21:38.297
♪ ♪

21:38.384 --> 21:42.518
Computer, just curious,

21:42.605 --> 21:45.565
how was I supposed to beat it?

21:45.652 --> 21:48.698
- The Kobayashi Maru
is a no-win scenario

21:48.785 --> 21:50.526
designed to test
how one reacts

21:50.613 --> 21:52.311
to a hopeless situation.

21:52.398 --> 21:55.009
- [laughs]

21:55.096 --> 21:56.532
Almost had it.

21:57.968 --> 21:59.492
Hey, guys.
Just wanted to say,

21:59.579 --> 22:01.929
I thought a lot about
what you told me this morning,

22:02.016 --> 22:02.973
and--

22:03.060 --> 22:06.150
what did I miss?

22:06.237 --> 22:07.413
- Data fragments.

22:07.500 --> 22:09.632
Corrupted but readable.

22:09.719 --> 22:12.766
The USS Protostar
was a prototype,

22:12.853 --> 22:14.681
fastest in Starfleet--

22:14.768 --> 22:16.117
- There's so much!

22:16.204 --> 22:18.598
It'll take months
to get through this raw data.

22:18.685 --> 22:22.079
- But answers may lie within.

22:22.166 --> 22:24.168
- Good thing Dal made us
go back for ya, huh?

22:24.255 --> 22:30.653
♪ ♪

22:30.740 --> 22:32.568
- Ooh. Who are they?

22:32.655 --> 22:33.961
[gasps]

22:34.048 --> 22:35.397
Whoa.

22:35.484 --> 22:40.184
♪ ♪

22:40.271 --> 22:42.012
- Mayday, mayday!

22:42.099 --> 22:44.014
This is Captain Chakotay
of USS Protostar.

22:44.101 --> 22:46.887
- Chakotay?
He's the captain?

22:46.974 --> 22:49.193
- Captain,
warning, we're being boarded!

22:49.280 --> 22:51.413
♪ ♪

22:51.500 --> 22:55.199
- I'm suddenly realizing...

22:55.286 --> 22:57.637
you aren't my first crew.

23:02.076 --> 23:05.166
[dramatic music]

23:05.253 --> 23:12.086
♪ ♪
